UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/104295739290001T
AB  - This paper shows that a debt contract with warrants for the lender and cash/equity settlement options for the entrepreneur-borrower is the optimal contract in a setting with moral hazard and unverifiable states of nature. This contract makes it possible to contract optimally ex ante on unverifiable states; debt obligations are adjusted to state realizations so that debt is made safer. Moral hazard is reduced as a result.
